Writing and Formatting Styles:
{
   "[Writing Styles] Likes": {"1": "Casual and friendly tone, e.g., 'Hey team, how's it going with the underwater hockey practice?'", "2": "Use of emojis to express excitement, e.g., 'Can't wait for the tournament! 🏊‍♂️🥇'", "3": "Informal wording that connects with the underwater hockey community, e.g., 'Let's dive into the details!'", "4": "Enthusiastic and upbeat vocabulary, e.g., 'We're making waves!'", "5": "Positive framing of challenges, e.g., 'Every game teaches us something new!"},
   "[Writing Styles] Dislikes": {"1": "Formal or overly professional language, e.g., 'Dear Sir or Madam,'", "2": "Overuse of jargon that may exclude newcomers, e.g., 'The biomechanics of the sport must be standardized.'", "3": "Negative language that discourages participation, e.g., 'If you don't practice, you'll never improve.'", "4": "Complex sentence structures that may confuse readers, e.g., 'Given the multifactorial dimensions of our underwater hockey strategies, we must consider...'", "5": "Impulsive writing that lacks coherence, e.g., 'So we played, and it was fun.'"},
   "[Formatting Styles] Likes": {"1": "Use of bullet points for clarity, e.g., 'Things to remember: 1) Bring gear, 2) Show up early!'", "2": "Subsections for different topics, e.g., 'Practice Schedule', 'Tournament Details'", "3": "Bold headings for important information, e.g., 'IMPORTANT: Safety Guidelines'", "4": "Personal signature at the end, e.g., 'Best, [Your Name], Underwater Hockey Enthusiast'", "5": "Short paragraphs for easy reading, e.g., 'Hi team! Just a quick note about our next practice. Looking forward to it!'"},
   "[Formatting Styles] Dislikes": {"1": "Long, dense paragraphs that are hard to read, e.g., 'In light of recent events, it is important to review the establishment of our underwater hockey strategies...'", "2": "Overly formal signatures, e.g., 'Sincerely, John Smith, Chief Organizer'", "3": "No headings or structure making it confusing, e.g., 'Here's the information for practice and tournaments.'", "4": "Inconsistent formatting or font styles, e.g., mixing Arial and Times New Roman", "5": "Neglecting the use of spacing, leading to cluttered text."

